  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is typically defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key legal elements usually include:\n\n1. Concealing the origin of funds obtained through criminal activities\n2. Transforming illegal proceeds into seemingly legitimate assets\n3. Disguising the source, ownership, or destination of illegally acquired money\n4. Intentionally conducting financial transactions to hide criminal proceeds\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but these are common core components of money laundering statutes.",
